<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-885-708  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 885 708.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC User  Oct 25 1989 n118 p25(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EMAP Business and Computer Publications1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft takes ASCII standard on board.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (standards).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Topic:     ASCIIWord Processing SoftwareStandardsImplementation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Microsoft takes ASCII standard on board More than six years after it launchedits flagship word processing product, Word, Microsoft has acceded to theASCII international standard.andM;According to Word product manager, Alan Dowzall, all future versions ofMicrosoft Word will be able to import printable ASCII text files,reformatting them according to the loaded style sheet.andM;The confirmation came just weeks after PC User, which has continued toquestion Microsoft on why Word has never been able to properly import ASCIItext files, took the case to Microsoft's chairman Bill Gates.andM;As an interim solution, Microsoft will supply a macro which will perform theformatting of ASCII files.andO;</TEXT></DOC>